-- Astrapak of South Africa Says Fire to Cut Supply, Production
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2013-01-08T15:55:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-08/astrapak-of-south-africa-says-fire-to-cut-supply-production.html
Astrapak Ltd. (APK) , a South African
plastic packaging manufacturer, said today that output will be
hurt following a fire at one of its facilities.  “We can confirm that both production and supply will be
affected” after the fire at the East Rand Plastics unit in
Brakpan, the Johannesburg-based company said in a statement
today. “There have been no injuries.”  The company supplies the food, beverage, pharmaceutical,
petrochemical, confectionery, fruit and general merchandise
markets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Johannesburg at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
